<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="110" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authority="Moratelli &amp; Dias, 2015" authorityName="Moratelli &amp; Dias" authorityYear="2015" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Lonchophylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lonchophylla inexpectata" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inexpectata">Lonchophylla inexpectata Moratelli &amp; Dias, 2015</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="110" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="110">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Lonchophylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lonchophylla inexpectata" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inexpectata">Lonchophylla inexpectata</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Caatinga, and has been recorded in the Brazilian states of Pernambuco and Bahia (
<bibRefCitation author="Moratelli, R" pageId="37" pageNumber="142" url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.514.10013" year="2015">Moratelli and Dias 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="110" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="110">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="110">
The red list of the IUCN ver. 3.1 has not yet evaluated the extinction risk of 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Lonchophylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lonchophylla inexpectata" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inexpectata">Lonchophylla inexpectata</taxonomicName>
. The species was not included in the official list of threatened species of Brazil (
<bibRefCitation author="Iack-Ximenes, GE" pageId="36" pageNumber="141" url="http://www.icmbio.gov.br/portal/images/stories/comunicacao/publicacoes/publicacoes-diversas/dcom_sumario_executivo_livro_vermelho_ed_2016.pdf" year="2016">ICMBIO-MMA 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Confirmed specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Lonchophylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lonchophylla inexpectata" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inexpectata">Lonchophylla inexpectata</taxonomicName>
are currently known from only three localities. Although an exhaustive revision of specimens housed in zoological collections might reveal a higher number of localities for the species, a provisional conservation status denoting some risk of extinction seems a sensible action considering the extremely low number of confirmed localities, particularly considering trends of habitat loss in the Caatinga (
<bibRefCitation author="Albuquerque, UP" pageId="30" pageNumber="135" url="https://doi.org/10.1100/2012/205182" year="2012">Albuquerque et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
